# ── Google Calendar ──────────────────────────────────────────
# The calendar where session bookings will appear.
# Share this calendar with your service account email
# (give it "Make changes to events" permission).
GOOGLE_CALENDAR_ID=ojaswi.wellness@gmail.com

# ── Google Spreadsheet ───────────────────────────────────────
# One Google Spreadsheet with TWO sheets inside:
#
#   Sheet 1 — "Therapist Capacity"  (admin fills via Google Form — once per day)
#     Columns: A=Timestamp | B=Date (YYYY-MM-DD)
#              C=Male Therapists | D=Female Therapists | E=Rooms Available
#     NOTE: No slot column — one entry per day covers all slots.
#
#   Sheet 2 — "Bookings"  (auto-created by the app on first booking)
#     Written automatically — do not edit manually.
#
# Steps to set up the admin Google Form:
#   1. Create a new Google Form at forms.google.com
#   2. Add questions:
#      Q1: Date (YYYY-MM-DD)       → Short answer
#      Q2: Male Therapists         → Short answer (number)
#      Q3: Female Therapists       → Short answer (number)
#      Q4: Rooms Available         → Short answer (number)
#   3. Responses → "Link to Sheets" → link to THIS spreadsheet
#      and rename the response sheet to "Therapist Capacity"
#   4. Share the spreadsheet with your service account email
#      (give it "Editor" permission)
#   5. Copy the spreadsheet ID from the URL:
#      https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/SPREADSHEET_ID/edit
GOOGLE_SPREADSHEET_ID=1eiyzUxD1Lgb0DxEdC4HtuMYk-axty3wGfX7Ke4vVJoI

# ── Gmail (for booking confirmation emails) ──────────────────
# Use a Gmail account (e.g. your business gmail) and a Google App Password.
# How to create an App Password:
#   1. Go to https://myaccount.google.com/security
#   2. Enable 2-Step Verification (required)
#   3. Search "App Passwords" → create one → choose "Mail"
#   4. Copy the 16-character password below (no spaces)
GMAIL_USER=ojaswi.wellness@gmail.com
GMAIL_APP_PASSWORD=pkfn mkpm xiee dpjy

